   {:e #blake3 "91dcd452af84770b7abb889bb737f4576596a65e898cd36eae9f504719a730de" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: braid observe list will group by concept. But concept names from HashEmbedder are hash artifacts like 'different-threshold-this' which provide zero steering value. An agent seeing '[different-threshold-this] (243 obs)' cannot determine the theme. This directly undermines C9-P5 ergonomics. PROBLEM: concept names are generated by TF-IDF over member observation text (concept.rs crystallize_concepts). With HashEmbedder, all observations share common vocabulary so TF-IDF produces meaningless keyword combinations. The concept NAME is a steering artifact — it must communicate the cluster's theme in 3-5 words. APPROACH: Add a concept_display_name(store, concept_entity) function that generates a human-readable name from the cluster's DISTINGUISHING keywords, not its most-common keywords. Algorithm: (1) Collect all observation bodies in this concept. (2) Collect all observation bodies NOT in this concept. (3) Compute TF-IDF where TF is within-concept and IDF is across-all-observations (not within-concept). (4) Top 3 keywords by TF-IDF score become the display name joined by hyphens. This produces names like 'stagnation-verification-sprint' instead of 'different-threshold-this' because 'stagnation' and 'verification' are distinctive to that cluster while 'store' and 'entity' appear everywhere. ALTERNATIVE considered: Just use the title of the highest-confidence member. Rejected because: it is one observation's perspective, not the cluster's theme. The TF-IDF approach captures what DISTINGUISHES this cluster from others. INTEGRATION: Used by format_agreement_summary(), format_concept_status(), and the new observe list grouping. Falls back to existing concept name if computation fails. ACCEPTANCE: (A) On the live store, concept that currently shows 'different-threshold-this' shows a meaningful 3-5 word name. (B) Names are deterministic (same store produces same names). (C) Names contain words that appear frequently IN the cluster but rarely OUTSIDE it. (D) Existing concept_inventory and format_concept_status still work. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs. EFFORT: 3h." :op :assert}
